-- Marshall Boya Advances After Winning Turkish Highway Auction
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-05-17T07:17:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-17/marshall-boya-advances-after-winning-turkish-highway-auction.html
Marshall Boya & Vernik Sanayii AS (MRSHL) , a
manufacturer of paint and other coatings, gained the most this
month after saying it won a 21.1 million lira ($11.6 million)
auction from the Turkish highways authority.  The shares jumped as much as 5.7 percent, the most since
April 30, to 55.75 liras and traded at 54.75 liras as of 10:08
a.m. in Istanbul.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
